# Prototype: Distill One Real Day of Sessions

## Question

Run pi distillation over one real day of fleet sessions using the decided
schema and redaction boundary. Land actual observation `.svx` pages, render
them on brain.joelclaw.com, and put the pages in front of Joel: are these
worth recalling? Measure compression ratio and token spend. The reaction
calibrates the noise bar and graduates the reflector + recall fog.

## Interim findings (2026-07-12, steering review — Joel's read pending)

Run: 75 qualifying sessions → 150 pages (ds4 + terra sets), 22 sensitive
(never rendered — verified), independent secret-scan clean, schema v1
conformant, zero .md. Index: /user/observations/2026-07-12-index/.

1. **Coverage collapses on monster sessions** — the 600k-token steering
   session got 4 bullets weighted to its tail. Build ticket: per-epoch
   chunking; big sessions become several atoms.
2. **Observations go stale by design** — a page recorded "inference is
   local" an hour before Joel amended to terra. Recall must rank durable
   decision pages above observations on conflict (temporal gradient,
   validated day one).
3. **Terra silently omitted 2 sessions in one batch** (retry recovered) —
   the sol orchestrator's deterministic completeness gate is load-bearing,
   not paranoia. Worker recommended ds4-as-distiller for this reason; the
   three-tier architecture absorbs terra's failure mode instead.
4. **`commits: []` on Claude sessions** — ledger is Pi-only; expanding it
   to Claude hooks buys real provenance.
5. **MDSvX brace escaping**: one page 500'd at prerender — distilled prose
   contained a literal `{editionId}` URL that compiled as a Svelte
   expression. The page-writer needs an escaping pass for `{` outside code
   spans. Page-scoped failure held (build succeeded, page skipped loudly).
